{
  "schema_version": "1.0",
  "name": "Common Emitter Amplifier",
  "description": "Classic CE amplifier with voltage divider bias. R1/R2 set Q-point. RE provides thermal stability. CE bypasses RE at AC. C1 input coupling, C2 output coupling. Gain ≈ −RC/re where re = 26mV/IC.",
  "notes": "Voltage divider bias: VB = VCC × R2/(R1+R2). VE = VB − 0.7V. IE ≈ IC = VE/RE. RC sets collector load. Gain Av ≈ −RC/(RE||re). CE bypasses RE at signal frequencies, increasing AC gain. C1/C2 block DC from source/load. 2N3904 typical: hFE=100–300.",
  "components": [
